        <p class="text-home">
          "Sambal lingkung" is one of the typical foods from Bangka Belitung
          that Moms can bring home as a souvenir. Its shape and texture are
          similar to shredded meat, but it is made from various fish such as
          small sharks, mackerel, mackerel tuna, or milkfish. These fish are
          steamed or boiled and then mashed. Then saut√©ed with various spices.
          "Sambal lingkung" can be served as a side dish for hot rice or used as
          filling for lemper (sticky rice rolls) and bread.
        </p>
