        <h3 class="text-right text-h3">Belacan</h3>
        <p class="text-home">
          Belacan is a typical food from Bangka Belitung that has a unique aroma
          and flavor because it is made from fermented marine products. Belacan
          is a kitchen seasoning made from ground shrimp that is then fermented.
          The process of making it is quite simple. Dried shrimp is ground and
          mixed with salt before being wrapped in banana leaves, then left to
          dry for several days.Belacan is one of the main ingredients for making
          sambal and can also be used as a seasoning in cooking.
        </p>
